<br>
I fight exclusively up on the top where the drakes and wyverns live.  After you take them to the beach and that last wyvern warp-gates to his bind spot,  you'll see why I do this.<br>
<br>
First, take care of all the drakes.  You will have one or possibly two drakes to kill to clear the area.  Killing drakes means you may get a gem or a hide, xp, and cash.<br>
<br>
Second, if you can find four wyverns, get an idea of which four you want.  Often, I'll staff-flux one and get two.  You'll learn when that is likely to happen.  Flux that wyvern first.  If to agro, great.<br>
<br>
Run, circle around to the next wyvern and staff it as you pass.  Be careful because you can be hit by the wyvern if you don't time it right.  Repeat for fourth wyvern.<br>
<br>
You're in a tight place, so lev helps a lot.  Learn the terrain up there and know where to run to circle.  Circle them up, run ahead, and snare.<br>
<br>
Now, it's PoF until they all die.  Resist rates are higher because you're using Frost on an Arctic beastie.  At 52, I would often have two wyverns, snared and coming at me, and I'd be OOM.  <br>
<br>
Keep a low level fire based DD ready if you can.  Often, in the two at me situation, the low level fire DD would finish off one and leave the last wyvern standing snared and waiting for me to finish it with my Icy wand.<br>
<br>
Chances are you'll have two more drakes to kill after you med full again after this quad.  It's drake, drake, quad, drake, drake, quad.....<br>
<br>
